HEADWORD: Dualist
<hw>Du"al*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>dualiste</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who believes in
dualism; a ditheist.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who administers two offices.</def> <rj><au>
Fuller.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dualistic</ent>⟦br⟧
